def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Extract index
    index = data.index

    # If the data is a DataFrame with MultiIndex
    if isinstance(data, DataFrame) and isinstance(index, MultiIndex):
        # If single level unstacking
        if isinstance(clocs, tuple):
            clocs = [index._get_level_number(lvl) for lvl in clocs]
            unstacked = data.unstack(clocs)
        # If multiple levels unstacking
        else:
            # Create a copy of the DataFrame
            dummy = data.copy()
            # Create a MultiIndex for the unstacked DataFrame
            new_index = index.droplevel(level=clocs[0]).unique()
            # Split and unstack the data
            unstacked = dummy.unstack(level=clocs[0], fill_value=fill_value)
            # Update the index
            unstacked.index = new_index
    # If the data is a Series
    elif isinstance(data, Series):
        # Unstack it and set the fill_value
        unstacked = data.unstack(fill_value=fill_value)
    else:
        return data

    return unstacked
